<details class="tool-instructions">
  <summary>Install — Mac</summary>
  <p>This app isn't signed with an Apple Developer certificate, so macOS will block it by default. Open Terminal, paste this command, and press Return:</p>
  <pre><code>xattr -cr ~/Downloads/Viewfinder.app</code></pre>
  <p>Then:</p>
  <ol>
    <li>Drag Viewfinder into your Applications folder</li>
    <li>Double-click to open</li>
  </ol>
</details>
<details class="tool-instructions">
  <summary>Install — Windows</summary>
  <p>Run <strong>Viewfinder Setup 1.0.0.exe</strong> to install — it adds Viewfinder to your Start Menu and installs it for the current user (no admin required).</p>
  <p>Or use the <strong>Portable</strong> version: just run <code>Viewfinder 1.0.0.exe</code> directly, no installation needed.</p>
  <p>Windows may show a SmartScreen warning since the app isn't signed — click <em>More info</em> then <em>Run anyway</em>.</p>
</details>
<details class="tool-instructions">
  <summary>Build from Source — Mac</summary>
  <ol>
    <li>Install Xcode Command Line Tools: <code>xcode-select --install</code></li>
    <li>Clone: <code>git clone https://github.com/justin-lawes/ViewfinderNative.git && cd ViewfinderNative</code></li>
    <li>Build: <code>find Viewfinder -name "*.swift" | sort | tr '\n' ' ' | xargs swiftc -o build/Viewfinder -framework Cocoa -framework AVFoundation -framework CoreMedia -framework CoreImage</code></li>
    <li>Install: <code>cp build/Viewfinder Viewfinder.app/Contents/MacOS/Viewfinder && cp -r Viewfinder.app /Applications/</code></li>
  </ol>
</details>
<details class="tool-instructions">
  <summary>Build from Source — Windows</summary>
  <ol>
    <li>Install <a href="https://nodejs.org">Node.js</a></li>
    <li>Clone: <code>git clone https://github.com/justin-lawes/ViewfinderPC.git && cd ViewfinderPC</code></li>
    <li>Install dependencies: <code>npm install</code></li>
    <li>Run: <code>npm start</code></li>
    <li>Build installer: <code>npm run build</code></li>
  </ol>
</details>
<details class="tool-instructions">
  <summary>Keyboard Shortcuts</summary>
  <ul class="tool-shortcuts">
    <li><kbd>Space</kbd> Play / Pause</li>
    <li><kbd>← →</kbd> Frame back / forward</li>
    <li><kbd>Shift + ← →</kbd> Skip 10s</li>
    <li><kbd>J / K / L</kbd> Shuttle reverse / stop / forward</li>
    <li><kbd>[ ]</kbd> Speed down / up</li>
    <li><kbd>T</kbd> Cycle timeline mode</li>
    <li><kbd>F</kbd> Toggle fullscreen</li>
    <li><kbd>D</kbd> Annotation mode</li>
    <li><kbd>C</kbd> Color picker</li>
    <li><kbd>;</kbd> Comments panel</li>
    <li><kbd>N</kbd> Add comment</li>
    <li><kbd>S</kbd> Screenshot to clipboard</li>
    <li><kbd>Alt + S</kbd> Screenshot to Desktop</li>
  </ul>
</details>
